-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2. verl-agent / GiGPO  (environment wrappers vendored)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Feng et al., "Group-in-Group Policy Optimization for LLM Agent Reinforcement
   Learning", arXiv:2505.10978. License: Apache-2.0.
   https://github.com/langfengQ/verl-agent
   FedAgent vendors verl-agent's WebShop/ALFWorld environment wrappers -- the
   action parsers (projection.py), the partition strategies (partition_strategy.py),
   and the ALFWorld AlfredTWEnv wrapper -- under fedagent/envs/{webshop,alfworld}/
   engine/. The rest of the verl-agent tree (its veRL fork, recipes, tests, and the
   unused gym_cards/sokoban/appworld environments) is not used and is not vendored.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. WebShop
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Yao et al., Princeton NLP. License: MIT.
   E-commerce agent benchmark. Vendored under fedagent/envs/webshop/engine/webshop/
   (web_agent_site + the shipped catalog data); its LICENSE.md is preserved there.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. ALFWorld
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Shridhar et al., Microsoft Research. License: MIT.
   Embodied household agent benchmark. Vendored under
   fedagent/envs/alfworld/engine/agent_system/environments/env_package/alfworld/alfworld/;
   an MIT LICENSE text matching the upstream ALFWorld terms (reconstructed; see the
   note at the top of the file) is preserved there.

   GPL component (disclosure): the vendored ALFWorld copy also includes the
   Metric-FF planner (Joerg Hoffmann) under
   .../env_package/alfworld/alfworld/gen/ff_planner/, whose C sources carry GNU
   General Public License v2-or-later headers. It is a standalone game-generation
   tool: it is NOT compiled, linked, or imported by FedAgent's Apache-2.0 code, and
   is NOT used by the released WebShop/ALFWorld experiments (which run on
   pre-generated game files fetched via download_data.sh). It is shipped only as mere
   aggregation; its GPL terms apply solely to that subdirectory, per the headers in
   its source files.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5. Bundled data derived from WebShop / ALFWorld
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   data/env_heterogeneity/ ships small data files derived from the WebShop and
   ALFWorld benchmark data (items 3-4 above, both MIT):
   - lookalike_data/*.json and holdout_webshop_v1.json, synthesized from WebShop's
     items_shuffle_1000.json / items_ins_v2_1000.json product data.
   - holdout_alfworld_v1.json, derived from the ALFWorld game data.
   These derived files are distributed under the same MIT terms as their source
   benchmark data, whose LICENSE texts are preserved in the vendored copies under
   fedagent/envs/{webshop,alfworld}/engine/.
